    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. so you mentioned the capacitor might be the problem? can you explain what a capacitor actually does in the unit? i'm kind of a novice with this stuff so i want to understand why it would cause that humming noise specifically.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A capacitor is a crucial component in your air conditioning unit's electrical system. Its primary function is to filter and regulate the flow of electrical current. In the context of your AC unit, the capacitor helps manage the AC power to the compressor and fan motor, allowing them to operate efficiently and effectively.\n\nWhen a capacitor fails, it can cause a build-up of electrical charge, which can disrupt the proper operation of the fan motor and compressor. This can lead to the motor vibrating or whining/mumbling, even if it's not spinning, due to the electrical inefficiencies and imbalances caused by the faulty capacitor.",
      "source": "target",
